<p><strong>LOS ANGELES</strong><span>Â -- Former South L.A. County Supervisor Yvonne Brathwaite Burke endorsed Eric Garcetti for Mayor today, citing his ability to deliver jobs and better city services to South L.A. and citywide.</span><br /><br /><span>"Eric Garcetti understands how to create jobs and solve problems in ways that truly revitalize communities. You can see the results he's delivered in Hollywood, Echo Park, Silver Lake, and Atwater Village. Eric is the best choice to create opportunity and stronger neighborhoods in South L.A. and all of Los Angeles," Burke said.</span><br /><br /><span>Burke represented the L.A. County Board of Supervisors 2nd District from 1992 to 2007. She previously served in the U.S. Congress and California State Assembly.</span><br /><br /><span>Garcetti has recently been endorsed by Congresswoman Karen Bass, Council President Herb Wesson and former South L.A. Councilmembers Nate Holden and Rita Walters. Garcetti is also endorsed by Councilmember and former mayoral candidate Jan Perry, Councilmember Bernard Parks, former Assemblymember Mike Davis, the New Frontier Democratic Club (the preeminent African American Democratic organization in Los Angeles) and the Los Angeles African American Women Political Action Committee. He has been endorsed by each of the three runoff candidates in the Mayor's race -- Perry, Kevin James and Emanuel Pleitez.</span></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 11 Apr 2013 12:00:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"http://www.ericgarcetti.com/former_supervisor_yvonne_brathwaite_burke_endorses_garcetti";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:33:"
      
      
      
      
    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:4:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"Former LA City Councilmember Ruth Galanter Endorses Eric Garcetti for Mayor";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1543:"<p><span>For Immediate Release</span><br /><span>April 9, 2013</span></p>
<div></div>
<p><span><strong>WESTSIDE</strong>Â -- Former LA City Councilmember Ruth Galanter today endorsed Eric Garcettiâs bid to become Los Angelesâ next mayor and will serve as co-chair of Westsiders for Garcetti with Councilmember Paul Koretz and Councilmember-elect Mike Bonin. Â Galanter served on the City Council from 1987 until 2003, representing the Westside communities of Venice, Mar Vista, Palms, Westchester, Playa del Rey, Del Rey, Westwood, and the Valley Communities of Van Nuys, Arleta, Panorama City, and Sun Valley. Â She is currently a visiting scholar at Loyola Marymount University and a lecturer at UCLA School of Public Health.</span><br /><br /><span>Galanter said, âI am proud to support Eric Garcetti for Mayor of Los Angeles. Â Ericâs record in public office shows a thoughtful commitment to protecting our environment, maintaining our city services and our economic health, and strengthening neighborhoods so that both residents and businesses can thrive. Â I am confident that as Mayor, Eric will consider the merits of each issue he addresses, not just who is for or against it.â</span><br /><br /><span>Garcetti said, âRuth Galanterâs endorsement is very special to me. Â We sat next to each other in my first year on the City Council and she taught me a lot about how City Hall works. Â I am honored to have her support in my campaign to create jobs and solve problems in every neighborhood of Los Angeles.â</span></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 09 Apr 2013 14:00:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://www.ericgarcetti.com/ruthgalanter";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:40:"
      
      
      
      
      
    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"Karen Bass Endorses Garcetti";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4791:"<p>For Immediate Release<br /> April 8, 2013</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Video: <a href="http://youtu.be/RETC5-6R7FI">http://youtu.be/RETC5-6R7FI</a></p>
<p>LOS ANGELES -- Congresswoman Karen Bass has endorsed Eric Garcetti for Mayor. Please see video at http://youtu.be/RETC5-6R7FI.</p>
<p>"I am happy to endorse Eric Garcetti for Mayor of Los Angeles. I have seen how he has created jobs and economic development in our city, and I know that as Mayor, he will do the same for South Los Angeles," Bass said.</p>
<p>Bass represents the 37th Congressional District, which includes South L.A., Mid City and Westside neighborhoods. She is a member of the Foreign Affairs and Judiciary Committees, in addition to serving as a member of the Democratic Caucus' Steering and Policy Committee and in a leadership role in the Congressional Black Caucus as Whip. She previously served as Speaker of the California State Assembly. A former Physician Assistant, she later founded and ran the Community Coalition, a community-based social justice organization in South Los Angeles addressing the drug and violence epidemic and engaging community residents in addressing the root causes of injustice.</p>
<p>On Saturday, Garcetti was endorsed by Council President Herb Wesson and former South L.A. Councilmembers Nate Holden and Rita Walters, who joined with Councilmember and mayoral candidate Jan Perry, Councilmember Bernard Parks and former Assemblymember Mike Davis in Leimert Park to fire up Garcetti volunteers headed out to knock on doors and phonebank. Please see release <a href="http://www.ericgarcetti.com/wesson_holden_walters_endorse_garcetti">http://www.ericgarcetti.com/wesson_holden_walters_endorse_garcetti</a></p>
<p>Garcetti has also been endorsed by the New Frontier Democratic Club, the preeminent African American Democratic organization in Los Angeles, and the Los Angeles African American Women Political Action Committee. He has been endorsed by each of the three runoff candidates in the Mayor's race -- Jan Perry, Kevin James and Emanuel Pleitez.</p>
<p>Garcetti is also endorsed by the Los Angeles Times; La OpiniÃ³n; Eastern Group Publications (including the Northeast Sun, Mexican American Sun, East LA Brooklyn Belvedere Comet and Wyvernwood Comet); Random Lengths and the UCLA Daily Bruin.</p>
<p>Garcetti has also been recently endorsed by: Councilmember Tom LaBonge; Assemblymember Ed Chau; Steve Soboroff; Councilmember Joe Buscaino, Councilmember Paul Krekorian; Councilmember Paul Koretz; Councilmember-Elect Mike Bonin; and Senator and CA Democratic Party Chair Art Torres (ret.).</p>
