<p>STUDIO CITY -- School Board Member and prosecutor Tamar Galatzan endorsed Eric Garcetti for Mayor today. Galatzan represents the 3rd LAUSD Board District, comprising Canoga Park, Chatsworth, Northridge, Reseda, Sherman Oaks, Studio City, Porter Ranch, and North Hills. She is an L.A. City Attorney with the Neighborhood Prosecutor Program assigned to the Van Nuys and North Hollywood Community Police Stations and was previously Western States Associate Counsel for the Anti-Defamation League. She announced her endorsement at the Porter Ranch Community School, a K-8 LAUSD school with a pilot engineering program that Garcetti and Galatzan toured.<br /><br /> "As a parent and a prosecutor, I know Eric Garcetti is the best choice to improve public schools and public safety in the Valley and across Los Angeles. I'm going to campaign hard for Eric to win the votes of my constituents and Angelenos citywide who want stronger schools and a stronger economy. I strongly endorse Eric Garcetti for Mayor."<br /><br /> "I am proud to have earned the endorsement of Tamar Galatzan. Safe streets and good schools are the cornerstones of a strong Los Angeles. As Mayor, I will fight to make sure every L.A. child gets an education that leads to college or a career. I want to prepare our kids for the jobs of tomorrow with science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) education. As a parent, I am personally invested in the fight for better schools."</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 05 Apr 2013 15:33:00 -0700";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://www.ericgarcetti.com/tamar_galatzan_endorses_eric_garcetti";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:13;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:33:"
      
      
      
      
