<div><span style="font-size: large;">Â </span></div>
<p><span>LOS ANGELES -- Eric Garcetti today received the endorsement of Councilmember Tom LaBonge, who is known for his deep L.A. roots, passion for Los Angeles and focus on nuts and bolts constituent services. LaBonge and Garcetti's districts are adjacent, and the two have worked together to dramatically revitalize neighborhoods like Hollywood, Silver Lake, and Atwater Village. They announced the endorsement at the Silver Lake Meadow, a dramatic new park they worked to create from unused DWP-owned land.</span><br /><br /><span>âI proudly endorse Eric Garcetti as the next mayor of Los Angeles because of his work in communities,â LaBonge said. âThereâs been a transformation of Hollywood and Silver Lake. It didnât happen because it just happened. It happened because of Ericâs leadership and desire. Eric has a track record of working with neighborhoods and creating things. You gotta know how to move bureaucracy and move the city and move community and Eric knows how to do that.â</span><br /><br /><span>"I am honored to have Tom LaBonge's endorsement," Garcetti said. "Tom and I share a deep connection to Los Angeles, and by working together across district lines, we've been able to deliver real results for our constituents and dramatically revitalize neighborhoods like Hollywood, Silver Lake and Atwater Village. As Mayor, I will bring government back to basics so it's focused on fixing people's problems and building stronger neighborhoods.âÂ </span><br /><br /><span>LaBonge represents the 4th Council District, which encompasses the Miracle Mile, Hancock Park, Windsor Square, Larchmont, Silver Lake, Los Feliz, Hollywood Hills, Laurel Canyon, Toluca Lake, Studio City, Mulholland Drive and Sherman Oaks. He was elected to the Council after the passing of Council President John Ferraro. LaBonge was a longtime Ferraro aide.</span></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4