<p>SOUTH L.A. -- Councilmember Bernard Parks endorsed Eric Garcetti for Mayor today, citing Garcettiâs independence and experience making tough decisions to balance the budget so that resources are available for important neighborhood services.</p>
<p>Parks made his announcement at Garcettiâs South L.A. headquarters at Crenshaw and Vernon.</p>
<p>âIâve worked with both candidates up close and know first-hand that Eric Garcetti is the best choice for Mayor. Eric has a demonstrated record creating jobs and solving problems for his constituents and has the independence necessary to balance our budget,â Parks said. âEric will be a Mayor who will create opportunity for my constituents and in every L.A. community. You can see the difference he can make in neighborhoods like Hollywood. I strongly endorse Eric Garcetti for Mayor.â</p>
<p>âBernardâs endorsement is especially meaningful during these tough economic times. As Budget and Finance Committee Chair, heâs been on the front lines, pushing for fiscal reform,â Garcetti said. âTogether, weâre going to win this race and balance our budget so we can get to work solving problems in South L.A. and across Los Angeles,â Garcetti said.</p>
<p>Garcetti is endorsed by the Los Angeles Times; La OpiniÃ³n; Eastern Group Publications (including the Northeast Sun, Mexican American Sun, East LA Brooklyn Belvedere Comet and Wyvernwood Comet); and the UCLA Daily Bruin.</p>
<p>Garcetti has recently been endorsed by: Councilmember Jan Perry; Assemblymember Mike Davis; Assemblymember Ed Chau; Steve Soboroff; Councilmember Joe Buscaino, Councilmember Paul Krekorian; Councilmember Paul Koretz; Councilmember-Elect Mike Bonin; Mayoral Candidate Emanuel Pleitez; and Senator and CA Democratic Party Chair Art Torres (ret.).</p>
