<p><span>SOUTH L.A. -- Councilmember and mayoral candidate Jan Perry endorsed Eric Garcetti for Mayor today in South L.A. Perry ran a strong mayoral primary campaign that attracted votes citywide, with particularly high levels of support among African Americans and Latinos and those seeking fiscally-responsible leadership for Los Angeles, which are critical constituencies in the runoff.</span><br /><br /><span>"I am proud to endorse Eric Garcetti for Mayor," Perry said. "I spent the last two years seeing the candidates up close. It's clear that the best choice for mayor is Eric Garcetti. Eric has the independence we need to balance the budget. Eric will bring opportunity to South L.A. and across Los Angeles just like he has in neighborhoods like Hollywood and Echo Park, which have been dramatically revitalized through his leadership."Â </span><br /><br /><span>"I am honored to have the endorsement of my friend Jan Perry," Garcetti said. "Jan brought an important, independent voice to the Mayor's race and I am proud her voice is joining with mine in calling for an efficient city government that's focused on creating jobs and solving problems for L.A. residents in every community. Together, we wrote the nation's largest clean water initiative and created the independent DWP ratepayer advocate, and now we are going to win this election to get our city back to work, balance our budget and expand opportunity here in South L.A. and across Los Angeles."</span><br /><br /><span>Garcetti and Perry spoke today at the historic 28th Street YMCA, which under Perry's leadership was repurposed into a supportive housing complex for emancipated foster youth and special needs adults. Built in 1926, the 28th Street YMCA was the city's first club founded by and for African Americans. Designed by famed architect Paul Williams, the building is listed on local, state and federal historic registers.</span></p>
