<div>
<h3><em>Angeles Chapter cites Gardea&#8217;s record on restoring L.A. RiverÂ and leading the fight for environmental justice and green jobs</em></h3>
<p align="left"><em><span id="more-461"></span> </em><strong>Los Angeles</strong><strong>-</strong>Â The Sierra Club, the nation&#8217;s largest and most influential grassroots organization, has endorsed Jose Gardea for the First City Council District.</p>
<div align="left">
<p>&#8220;The Sierra Club is proud to endorse Jose Gardea for City Council District 1,&#8221; said Susana Reyes of the national Sierra Club Board and endorsement team leader, L.A. County political committee. &#8220;Jose has a proven record of working effectively for the people of this district, protecting the integrity of neighborhoods, preserving and expanding local parks and open space, and supporting smart growth that creates good jobs.&#8221;</p>
<p>Gardea, who has served as Chief Deputy to current Councilman Ed P. Reyes, has helped create over 100 acres of brand new park space in the First Council District. As a leading local advocate for environmental justice, Gardea has worked to reduce pollution and expand open space in impacted communities, which tend to be poorer.</p>
<p>&#8220;We are particularly impressed with Gardea&#8217;s leadership for and commitment to the L.A. River Master Plan, which includes ambitious and necessary pollution prevention and recreational elements in communities that need them most,&#8221; Reyes continued.</p>
<p>&#8220;I am honored to have the trust and endorsement of the Sierra Club and look forward to working with them on a plan to create more green jobs in the First Council District.&#8221;</p>
<p>Despite a nearly 2-to-1 spending advantage by Gardea&#8217;s opponent, with nearly a $1 million spent against him, including funding by Chevron Corporation, Gardea charged forward with a strong grassroots campaign, and enters the runoff campaign with momentum.</p>
<p>Gardea joins Sierra Club endorsed candidates for the upcoming May 21, 2013 general elections: Eric Garcetti, Mayor; Mike Feuer, City Attorney, Cindy Montanez, Sixth Council District, and Mitch O&#8217;Farrell, Thirteenth Council District.</p>
<p>Gardea is the only candidate supported by the United Farm Workers Co-founder Dolores Huerta, the Los Angeles Times and the Los Angeles League of Conservation Voters.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">###</p>
<p>The Angeles Chapter is the local voice of the Sierra Club, America&#8217;s oldest, largest and most influential grassroots environmental organization. Its 40,000 members in Los Angeles and Orange Counties strive to explore, enjoy and protect nature in their communities and the planet.Â  Learn more about the Angeles Chapter atÂ <a href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001PUr8_WTxTUUyiTNVri4daSl2L4O6HQeUU-3C1T_VfrmjJJIO-sOHqcB20Nvii0_nD-C276uYIovLIxzSgE5saL350oxlxE0boBxjvq6W_oL0wk4QoNfts8i2BnhAmmV_" target="_blank" shape="rect">www.angeles.sierraclub.org</a>.</p>
