p>
<p><span id="more-451"></span></p>
<p>Los Angeles must be a full partner in integrating families as they begin the process of citizenship.</p>
<p>While the federal government holds the ultimate responsibility for immigration reform, it is important to remember that we have many entry points available here at the city level which can help families access information and services through our existing Worksource centers, Family Source centers, Youth Source centers and public libraries.</p>
<p>Thatâs why as chief deputy, I helped secure funding for these facilities because I understand their importance to integrating families into our neighborhoods.</p>
<p>As councilmember, I will further support the full funding and policy integration of The Office of Immigration Services to coordinate all existing and new services for our community and continue the work we have already started.</p>
<p>Together, we can build a strong city.</p>
<p>Jose Gardea<br />
Candidate for City Council, District 1</p>
