";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3259:"<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Cedillo campaign in trouble, as Gardea raises over $100,000 andÂ heads into runoff with $60,000+ lead in cash-on-hand</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span id="more-434"></span></p>
<p style="text-align: right;">Contact: Steve Barkan<br />
steve@sgacamp.com<br />
(626) 535-9616 x2</p>
<p style="text-align: right;">Â (323) 533-3106</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">In the City&#8217;s closest Council race, Jose Gardea has jumped out to a big fundraising lead, building a significant advantage in both money raised and cash-on-hand for the first reporting period in the General Election.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s how the numbers breakdown:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Money raised</strong><br />
Gardea $101,775 &#8211; Cedillo $61,634</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ending Cash Balance</strong> (with Matching Funds)<br />
Gardea $125,325 &#8211; Cedillo $68,301.05</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Outstanding Debt</strong><br />
Gardea $20,931.06 &#8211; Cedillo $24,184.87</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Real Cash-on-Hand</strong> (Ending Balance minus Outstand Debt)<br />
Gardea $104,393.94 &#8211; Cedillo $44,116.18</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">&#8220;While Jose Gardea continues to grow his support, Cedillo has run out of gas,&#8221; said Steve Barkan of SG&amp;A Campaigns, who is Gardea&#8217;s consultant. &#8220;The powerful special interests behind Cedillo &#8211; like Chevron, Walmart and Farmers Insurance &#8211; were betting on him to win in the primary. Cedillo&#8217;s supporters and donors were shocked by the outcome, and apparently now they are re-thinking their support.&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;Cedillo&#8217;s collapse in fundraising mirrors what we witnessed during the last few weeks of the primary campaign: a collapse in support from voters,&#8221; Barkan continued. &#8220;Once voters learn that Cedillo is not who they thought he was, and that Jose Gardea is the right person for this job, Cedillo&#8217;s big initial lead evaporated.&#8221;</p>
<p>Despite a nearly 2-to-1 spending advantage in the primary for Cedillo, with $906,933 spent on his behalf, Gardea came out of nowhere to win 43.45% of the vote and force a runoff. (spending for Cedillo is on the verge of passing a million dollars, a first for the 1st Council District) &#8220;It&#8217;s clear that our opponent has maxed out his support,&#8221; said Barkan. &#8220;When a candidate is far better known, has such a huge financial advantage, and has to spend twice as much per vote &#8211; he has reached his limit of support and is in trouble.&#8221;</p>
<p>Gardea is the only candidate in the race endorsed by the trio of popular local Councilmembers &#8211; Ed Reyes, Eric Garcetti and Jose Huizar. He&#8217;s also supported by Assemblymember Jimmy Gomez, United Farm Workers co-founder Dolores Huerta, The Los Angeles Times, The Latin American Law Enforcement Association, The Northeast Democratic Club, United Food and Commercial Workers Local 770, Laborers Local 300 and hundreds of local community leaders.</p>
<p>For more information about Jose Gardea for City Council, please visit www.josegardea2013.com.</p>
