:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2768:"<p align="center"><strong>Dolores Huerta Endorses Jose Gardea for City Council</strong></p>
<p align="center"><em>Labor leader, civil rights activist and co-founder of the United Farm Workers, cites Gardeaâs commitment to people over politics.</em></p>
<p><em></em>Dolores Huerta, co-founder of the United Farm Workers, endorsed Jose Gardea just days after Gardea successfully overcame the odds, and forced a special interest funded candidate with $800,000+ behind him into the runoff.<span id="more-356"></span></p>
<p><em>âI support Jose Gardea because he is on the side of the people â not the corporations. Jose fights for good jobs and working families, and has the courage we need on City Council to stand up to the special interests. And Jose Gardea is the ONLY candidate who knows and understands the needs and concerns of the families in CouncilÂ District Oneâ</em> said Dolores Huerta. <em>âOver the past two decades Jose has stood up for our neighborhoodsÂ and working families. Â I am proud to support Jose Gardea. Jose is the neighborhood candidateÂ and clearly the best choice for our communities.â</em></p>
<p>Gardea moves into the runoff election with clear advantage in momentum, endorsements and fundraising.Â  With only 816 votes separating him from his opponent, the message voters sent to the powerful special interests was crystal clear: They will not allow special interests such as Chevron and Walmart to buy their Council District, no matter how much they spend.</p>
<p>â<em>Dolores Huerta embodies the spirit of the people of Council District 1,â</em> said Gardea. <em>âDolores Huertaâs commitment to working families, civil and community rights has inspired me throughout my life and I am honored to have her support.â</em></p>
<p>Gardea is the only candidate in the race to have the endorsement of all three local Councilmembers Ed Reyes, Eric Garcetti and Jose Huizar; Assemblymember Jimmy Gomez; the L.A. Times, the Northeast Democratic Club and hundreds of local leaders.</p>
<p>Gardea, Chief Deputy to Councilmember Reyes, was born and raised in the First District and has served its communities for more than two decades. Gardea was instrumental in creating the cityâs first local gang injunction to stop the violence.Â  He has directed City resources to build new police and fire stations, as well as new parks, schools and libraries in First District neighborhoods.</p>
<p>Born and raised in the First District, Jose attended local schools and graduated from UCLA. He lives in Northeast Los Angeles with his wife, Susana, and their two sons, Zacharias and Sebastian. For more information about Jose Gardea for City Council, please visit <a href="http://www.josegardea2013.com">www.josegardea2013.com</a>.</p>
