<p><span style="color: #000000;">I want to take this opportunity to thank each and every one of you for your help Tuesday â and in the months leading up to Election Day.Â  With your support we overcame the odds, and forced a well-known career politician with $800,000 behind him into the runoff, closing the margin to only 816 votes. Together we will win this race in May and keep our district moving forward.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span id="more-348"></span>The message voters sent to the powerful special interests was crystal clear: We will not allow special interests such as Chevron and Walmart to buy our Council District, no matter how much they spend.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">You can count on me to continue to stand on the side of the people of the 1<sup>st</sup> Council District, and I will not be intimidated by the big polluters and corporations.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">You can count on me to continue to fight for parks and open space, affordable housing, libraries and police and fire stations for our community, sensible transportation, and better service from City government. I will put local job creation and small businesses ahead of giving away special privileges to out-of-town corporations.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">And I will not stand by and allow the integrity and quality of life in our neighborhoods be trampled on by those trying to build a freeway through the heart of our community, or another Walmart, or billboard blight, or massive poorly planned developments like the condos planned for the Barlow Hospital grounds.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">I will need you to win this fight. Iâm glad to have you on my side.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Again, I thank you for your support and look forward to seeing you at our campaign office very soon!</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Sincerely,</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;">Jose Gardea</span><br />
<span style="color: #000000;"> Candidate, First Council District</span></p>
