<p>Contact: Steve Barkan, 626.535.9616 x2, 323.533.3106 or George Magallanes, 213.308.4791</p>
<p>Newly elected Assemblymember, Jimmy Gomez, joined local Councilmembers Ed P. Reyes and Jose Huizar in supporting Jose Gardea for City Council in District 1.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">âI am proud to support Jose Gardea for City Council. Jose Gardea is committed to public safety, economic development and neighborhood services,â said Assemblymember Gomez. âI look forward to working closely with Jose on a neighborhood agenda that keeps our streets safe and delivers quality services to our communities.â</p>
<p>With the endorsement of Assemblymember Gomez, Gardea becomes the clear choice for local leaders in the race for Council District 1.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">âI am honored to have earned the endorsement of Assemblymember Gomez,â said Jose Gardea. âI look forward to working with him to keep our neighborhoods safe and our local economy strong.â</p>
<p>Gardea, Chief Deputy to Councilmember Reyes, was born and raised in the First District and has served its communities for more than two decades. Gardea was instrumental in creating the cityâs first gang injunction to stop the violence. He has directed City resources to build new police and fire stations, as well as new parks, schools and libraries in First District neighborhoods.</p>
<p>Jose attended local schools and graduated from UCLA. He lives in Northeast Los Angeles with his wife, Susana, and their two sons, Zacharias and Sebastian For more information about Jose Gardea for City Council, please visit www.josegardea2013.com.</p>
